properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued February 7 at 7:26PM CST until February 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...SNOW EXPECTED LATE SATURDAY NIGHT INTO SUNDAY ACROSS SOUTHERN
MINNESOTA INTO WISCONSIN...

.A Winter Storm Watch for moderate to heavy snow remains in
effect for southern Minnesota into Wisconsin, along and south of a
line from Redwood Falls to Red Wing Minnesota to Eau Claire
Wisconsin from late Saturday night into Sunday. Snowfall amounts
of 6 inches or greater appear possible in the Watch area. The
heaviest snow will be Sunday morning.

The winter storm watch means be prepared, hazardous winter
weather is possible. Travel impacts are expected as roads become
snow covered and slippery. Winds will be fairly light, with only
minor blowing or drifting.

* WHAT...Moderate to heavy snow possible. Total snow
accumulations of 4 to 7 inches possible.

* WHERE...Pepin and Eau Claire Counties.

* WHEN...From Sunday morning through Sunday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions and impacts to
travel.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM SUNDAY MORNING THROUGH SUNDAY AFTERNOON
